The conceptual foundations of the Malthusian theory were formed by Thomas Malthus,[82] and a modern representation of these approach is provided by Ashraf and Galor.[83] In line with the predictions of the Malthusian theory, a cross-country analysis finds a significant positive effect of the technological level on population density and an insignificant effect on income per capita significantly over the years 1â€“1500.[83]
